        "title": "fix(security): strip apiKey from models.json (Layer 1: #11829)",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nCloses #11829 (Layer 1)\n\nStrips \\^GpiKey\\ from provider configs before writing to \\models.json\\. API keys are resolved at runtime via env vars and auth profiles - they do not need to be persisted in the model catalog file. Removing them prevents accidental leakage to LLM prompt context.\n\n## Changes\n\n- \\src/agents/models-config.plan.ts\\: strip \\^GpiKey\\ field from each provider entry before JSON serialization\n\n## Verification\n\n- Existing provider auth resolution (env vars, auth profiles) is unaffected\n- Only the persisted \\models.json\\ file is sanitized\n- Runtime key lookup paths are unchanged",
